 **Problem description:**
`Slider.Ticks` is a `DoubleCollection`, but in xaml binding syntax, it allows binding to `IReadOnlyList<double>`, and there's not any binding errors at run time. This makes one think that the binding has been successful, but the ticks drawing is wrong.

Also discussed here: https://github.com/HandyOrg/HandyControl/issues/1269

**Relative codes**:
```cs
public class RootViewModel : PropertyChangedBase {
    public IReadOnlyList<double>? Ticks { get; set; }

    public double MinStrike { get; set; }

    public double MaxStrike { get; set; } = 10;

    public double StartStrike { get; set; }

    public double EndStrike { get; set; }

    public void UpdateTicks() {
        Ticks = new[] { 1d, 2d, 5d, 20d, 50d, 200d };

        StartStrike = MinStrike = Ticks[0];
        EndStrike = MaxStrike = Ticks[^1];
    }
}
```

```xaml
<hc:RangeSlider IsSnapToTickEnabled="True" Ticks="{Binding Ticks}" TickPlacement="Both"
                hc:TipElement.Visibility="Visible" hc:TipElement.Placement="Bottom"
                Minimum="{Binding MinStrike}" Maximum="{Binding MaxStrike}" 
                ValueStart="{Binding StartStrike}" ValueEnd="{Binding EndStrike}" />
<Slider Margin="0 20 0 0" IsSnapToTickEnabled="True" Ticks="{Binding Ticks}" TickPlacement="Both" 
        Minimum="{Binding MinStrike}" Maximum="{Binding MaxStrike}" />
<Button Margin="0 20 0 0" Content="Update Ticks" Command="{s:Action UpdateTicks}" />
```

 **Actual behavior:** <!-- callstack for crashes / exceptions -->
 The ticks are drawn incorrectly, and there are no binding errors.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4510984/194559728-97d846b4-1175-4d0e-8909-8862d0584cb5.png)


 **Expected behavior:**
`Slider.Ticks` accepts `IReadOnlyList<double>` for drawing ticks, or show binding errors at run time in Visual Studio Binding Error window.
 
